name: environmental-regulation
notes: KR305b 1994 coverage, used to support water quality programs, references water quality use designations and support levels. The KR305b 1994 coverage is available for the Kansas Lower Republican basin. Kansas Uses and the National Pollution Discharge Elimination System (NPDES) coverage, are both used to support water quality programs. The Kansas Uses coverage references water quality use support designations across the state, and the NPDES coverage is a partial representation of the major and minor treatment facility locations across Kansas. The Landfills coverage, used to support the environmental quality program, references solid waste landfill sites and waste management practices across the state. Each coverage's data is current as of publication date. The related KDHE operational databases are dynamic databases.

["Use Constraints: Data is current as of publication date. KDHE is not responsible for database integrity following download and publication. To be used at minimum scale of 1:100,000. Please be advised that the Kansas Open Records Act (KORA), K.S.A. 45-215 et seq. and K.S.A. 21-3914, prohibit the commercial use of the facility list by any person. Any person who receives a list of names and addresses for the purpose of selling or offering to sell any property or service to listed persons may be found guilty of a Class C misdemeanor except in the limited circumstances provided for in K.S.A. 21-3914.
